  "prompt": "How do you get Chromecast to work with Xfinity hotspots?",
  "response": "To use Chromecast with Xfinity hotspots, follow these steps:\n\n1. Connect to the Xfinity WiFi hotspot with your mobile device or laptop\n\n2. Open the Xfinity WiFi login page:\n- Usually this happens automatically when you connect\n- If not, open a web browser and try to load a website\n- You should be redirected to the login page\n\n3. Log in using your Xfinity account credentials:\n- Username/email\n- Password\n- Or Xfinity ID\n\n4. Accept terms of service and complete login\n\n5. Connect your Chromecast to the same Xfinity WiFi network\n- Go to Chromecast settings\n- Select the Xfinity hotspot network\n- Enter login credentials if prompted\n\n6. Verify connection by trying to cast from a supported app\n\nTroubleshooting tips:\n- Ensure you have a valid Xfinity account\n- Check network signal strength\n- Restart Chromecast and device if needed\n- Make sure you're within range of the hotspot\n\nNote: Some Xfinity hotspots may have limitations or require additional authentication steps.",
